title: Deploy Concourse
---

This topic describes setting up Concourse for 
1. From the offline Ops Manager, upload the releases and stemcell for the Concourse installation:
<p class="terminal">
$ bosh -n upload release /opt/artifacts/releases/concourse-0.62.0.tgz
</p>
<p class="terminal">
$ bosh -n upload release /opt/artifacts/releases/garden-linux-0.308.0.tgz
</p>
<p class="terminal">
$ bosh -n upload stemcell /opt/artifacts/stemcells/bosh-stemcell-2989-aws-xen-ubuntu-trusty-go_agent.tgz --skip-if-exists
</p>

1. Modify the Concourse Deployment Manifest `p-concourse-chiron.yml` in the deployments directory on the offline Ops Manager to suit the environment. Configure the following parameters as necessary:
    1. Director UUID: Use value from \<BOSH-STATUS>  above
    1. Network Cloud Properties:
    	1. Subnet-ID: Use value from pcf-private-subnet
    	1. AWS Console: Use VPC value

1. Set deployment:
<p class="terminal">
$ bosh -n deployment /home/ubuntu/workspace/dark-chiron-aws/deployments/p-concourse-chiron.yml
</p>

1. Deploy Concourse:
<p class="terminal">
$ bosh -n deploy
</p>

1. Run BOSH utilities to confirm successful deployment:
<p class="terminal">
$ bosh -n vms p-concourse-chiron
$ bosh -n cck --report
</p>

<p class="note"><strong>Note</strong>: This deployment contains no BOSH errands.</p>
